This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the acquisition of an action model for intelligent agents. The use of long short-term memory (LSTM) techniques also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sequence labelling capabilities, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP), indicating that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The fact that the paper deals with planning and scheduling also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
